            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>303</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>109</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1986"/><citedRange>137</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>72, 77, 100, 131</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">in this very water ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>143</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... those were householders in previous births ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Und sie glühen in den [wtl. durch die] Flammen [und] erdulden furchtbare Leiden.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">And they glow in [lit. through] the flames [and] endure dreadful suffering.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>201</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>56</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:meunier2013"/><citedRange>160, 175</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ils faisaient peu de cas des autres et ne faisaient pas de don ni d'action méritoire.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Sie machten die anderen verächtlich, gaben nicht Gabe [und] erwarben sich nicht Verdienst.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">They ridiculed others, did not give gift[s] [and] did not gain merit for themselves.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>435, 464</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">but ... the householders will be gathered at that time</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">but … the householders will be gathered at that time</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>278</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>235</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 87 || In the Maitreyāva-</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">dānavyākaraṇa the 22<hi rend="superscript">nd</hi> chapter named Āgārikanarakopapatti: ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>137</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Who wants to (be freed?) from the hells,</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6 #b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Who wants to (be freed?) from the hells, or who has this wish, «may I obtain divine happiness!», or who has the wish, «… human and divine …» </seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>268</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>115</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">or who has this wish, «may I obtain divine happiness!», or who has the wish, «... human and divine ...»</seg></seg></choice></p>
